  "local_port": 58716,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am planning a 4 day Holiday in North India. Where can I go?",
  "response": "North India offers a variety of destinations that cater to different interests, whether you're looking for natural beauty, historical sites, or cultural experiences. Here are some travel suggestions for a 4-day holiday:\n\n1. **Delhi & Agra:**\n   - **Day 1-2: Delhi** - Explore historical landmarks such as the Red Fort, Qutub Minar, India Gate, Humayun\u2019s Tomb, and Lotus Temple. Wander through vibrant markets like Chandni Chowk and Connaught Place.\n   - **Day 3-4: Agra** - Visit the iconic Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, and Fatehpur Sikri. You can travel to Agra by train or car from Delhi.\n\n2. **Jaipur (Rajasthan):**\n   - Spend your days exploring the Pink City\u2019s majestic palaces and forts, including the City Palace, Hawa Mahal, Amer Fort, and Jantar Mantar. Don\u2019t forget to shop for local handicrafts and enjoy traditional Rajasthani cuisine.\n\n3. **Shimla & Manali (Himachal Pradesh):**\n   - **Day 1-2: Shimla** - Walk around the Mall Road, visit the Christ Church, Jakhoo Temple, and enjoy the scenic views from Kufri.\n   - **Day 3-4: Manali** - Head to Rohtang Pass (if open), Solang Valley, Hadimba Temple, and Old Manali. Engage in adventure activities like paragliding and river rafting.\n\n4. **Rishikesh & Haridwar (Uttarakhand):**\n   - **Day 1-2: Rishikesh** - Experience the spiritual vibe with yoga and meditation sessions, visit the iconic Lakshman Jhula, and enjoy river rafting on the Ganges.\n   - **Day 3-4: Haridwar** - Attend the evening Ganga Aarti at Har Ki Pauri, visit Mansa Devi Temple, and explore the local bazaars.\n\n5. **Amritsar (Punjab):**\n   - Spend your days visiting the Golden Temple, Jallianwala Bagh, and Wagah Border. Enjoy the local Punjabi cuisine and shop for traditional items.\n\n6. **Kashmir (Jammu & Kashmir):**\n   - **Day 1-2: Srinagar** - Enjoy a Shikara ride on Dal Lake, visit Mughal Gardens, and explore the local markets.\n   - **Day 3-4: Gulmarg or Pahalgam** - Engage in activities like trekking, skiing (if visiting in winter), and enjoy the breathtaking landscapes.\n\nThese destinations offer a mix of cultural, historical, and natural attractions, ensuring a memorable holiday experience.",
